description:
Reverse-engineer and document the complete database schema of the 'DrTuxTest' MySQL database (user: root, password: empty). Generate a comprehensive JSON documentation file at ~/Documents/drtuxtest_schema.json including accurate column definitions, row counts, and summary statistics.

The JSON must follow this structure:
{
  "database": "DrTuxTest",
  "total_tables": <integer>,
  "tables": [
    {
      "name": "<table_name>",
      "row_count": <integer>,
      "columns": [
        {
          "name": "<column_name>",
          "type": "<data_type>",
          "nullable": <true|false>,
          "key": "<PRI|MUL|UNI|empty_string>",
          "default": "<value_or_null>"
        }
      ],
      "indexes": ["<index_name_1>", ...]
    }
  ],
  "top_5_largest_tables": [
    {"name": "<table_name>", "row_count": <integer>}
  ],
  "summary": {
    "total_rows_all_tables": <integer>,
    "tables_with_data": <integer>,
    "empty_tables": <integer>
  }
}
